(Match 436)  25th February 1981  (World Cup Qualifying Group 6)
ISRAEL - SCOTLAND  0-1  (0-0)
Referee:   Otto Andreco (Romania)
Crowd:     35.000, National Stadium, Ramat Gan 
Goal:      0-1 Dalglish (54)
ISRAEL:  (Coach:  Jack Mansell)
Yossi Mizrahi - Gadi Machnes, Haim Bar, Avraham (Avi) Cohen, Jacob Cohen - Nissim Cohen, 
Yaacov Ekhoiz, Itzhak Shum, Moshe Sinai - Gidi Damti, Beni Tabak.

SCOTLAND:  (Manager:  John (Jock) Stein/27)
Alan Roderick Rough             (38/Partick Thistle) -
Daniel Fergus McGrain                            (50/Celtic)
Francis Tierney Gray                                         (11/Nottingham Forest)
Graeme James Souness                                                             (19/Liverpool)
Alexander McLeish                                                                            (8/Aberdeen) - 
Kenneth Burns                                                                                                    (18/Nottingham Forest)
John Wark                                                                                                                             (10/Ipswich Town)
Kenneth Mathieson Dalglish           (78/Liverpool) -
Steven Archibald                          (6/Tottenham Hotspur)
Archibald Gemmill [c]                          (42/Birmingham City)
John Neilson Robertson                                             (13/Nottingham Forest)

Subs:
William Fergus Miller                (10/Aberdeen)                 for John Wark        (46 Minutes)
Andrew Mullen Gray                                                      (11/Wolverhampton Wanderers)  for Kenneth Dalglish (69 Minutes)
       
Notes:  Daniel McGrain is the 5th player to reach 50 caps for Scotland.
                       


